content.rendered:
Origin:

KC 33® Feminized is a sativa/indica stable marijuana hybrid of Thai and Brazil.

Charactaristics:

While designed specificly for outdoor growing, stable genes make her seeds ideal for indoor also. Being sativa dominated, the KC 33® Feminized cannabis strain behaves like a typical sativa. The seeds produce tall thin plant with narrow light green leaves and chunky thick buds. Her Thai and Brazil ancestors gave her some characteristics of a traditional cannabis landrace. As both came from countries with quite a mild climate, KC 33® Feminized cannabis seeds are highly resistant to mushrooms and plague and quite tolerant to irrigation.

Size:

Outside: Sizes of up to a massive 3.75 m to 4 meters are no exception,
Inside:, When grown inside the avarage size is usually controlled and kept below 100 cm.

For the best result place the KC 33® in a sunny spot as this strain takes a little longer to grow and mature and also requires more light than other strains.

Flowering:

The flowering stage lasts between 10 to 16 weeks outside and just 6 to 9 weeks indoor. After a flowering period, enriched with a smell of fresh citrus and sweet spices, first buds come up, making the smell more intense. Then you can enjoy harvesting the aromatic, sugary, aminoacids and cannabinoids marijuana buds for 75-80 days. KC 33® Feminized buds are said to produce double THC and make it as high as 20-22%.

Yield:

Average outside yield is unbelievably high and can go up to around 900 gr. per plant. You can start your harvest at the end of September and continue throughout the whole month of October.
Indoor plants will give you as much as 130 gr. per plant.

Additional Information:

Medicine produced from this type of cannabis have a lower CBD and higher THC count which produces a more clear headed, energetic effect.

K.C. Brains Leda Uno® Feminized is one of the most powerful marijuana strains around and is a stable hybrid of a male K.C. 33® and a female Brazilian. After that it was crossed with a KC 606 early flowering male crossed with Leda Uno®

Charactaristics:

Being sativa dominated, Leda Uno® Feminized behaves like a typical sativa. The seeds produce tall thin plant with narrow light green leaves and chunky thick buds. This marijuana variety is very resistant to pests. The superb cross of ancestors make this strain ideal for both indoor and outdoor growing.

Size:

Outside: average size can reach up to 3 m.
Inside:,  inside varieties of this marijuana will keep their height under control and won’t stretch taller than 150 cm.

For the best result place the Leda Uno® in a sunny spot as this strain takes a little longer to grow and mature and also requires more light than other strains.

Flowering:

The flowering stage is relatively short and lasts only 8 to 10 weeks outside, while indoor takes from 6 to 8 weeks.

When flowering, Leda Uno® Feminized smells beautifully and will not stink you out of your home. After her buds reach their maturing stage, they will start spreading a more intense and incredibly pleasant lemon aroma which will also remain in the dried product.

Yield:

Leda Uno® Feminized is a really great yielder and produces as much as 800 gr. of a quality product per plant when grown outside while indoor yields around on avarage 150gr. per plant can be reached when properly taken care off.

The dried product is very easy to keep and has a long shelf life.

Additional Information:

Medicine produced from this type of cannabis have a lower CBD and higher THC count which produces a more clear headed, energetic effect.

K.C. Brains cannabis seeds are thoroughly selected and can guarantee almost 80% of germination.

Charactaristics:

KC 36® Feminized weed has a strong, skunky smell and the taste includes notes of tropical fruit and citrus. This is one of those weeds that has a powerful physical hit and smokers, particularly inexperienced ones, may well find themselves locked to the couch for a period.

Size:

KC 36® Feminized seeds produce plants that grow to about 175 centimetres outdoors, with dark green leaves that are notably broad. Plants are multi-branched and irregular while the buds are dense and covered in silvery crystals. Indoors, the plants grow shorter, about 75 centimetres, but have the same irregular growth pattern. THC content is high.

Flowering:

The flowering stage is relatively short and lasts only 6 to 9 weeks outside, while indoor takes about 1 week shorter and takes 6 to 8 weeks. Harvest from end of September until half October.

Yield:

Outdoor harvest comes in late September and you can expect yields of around 900 grams per plant. Indoors, the plants can be grown in hydro or soil and flowering time is six to eight weeks. Indoor yields are lower than outdoor ones.

Additional Info:

Medical practitioners recommend this strain for people who find it difficult to relax or have problems with sleeping.
